            "good_executions": [
                {
                    "video_time": 1.609394,
                    "list": "[\"I like all the prep that's going into it.\", \"She is not only looking at the hold, she's also brushing the hold.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 1.740772,
                    "list": "['this climber is showing that she has an understanding of what that means by brushing the hold and she wants to have better grip with these handholds']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 1.792035,
                    "list": "['This climber starts by brushing the holds.']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 18.153352,
                    "list": "['climber is brushing the holds', 'climber doing good due diligence here and making sure they understand the boulder', 'making sure that the holds on the wall are clean']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 23.309611,
                    "list": "['climber is reading her route', 'chalking up her hands']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 26.380577,
                    "list": "['She is wiping the chalk from her hands', \"It's going to remove any excess chalk from her hands that might cause her to slip\", 'giving her a nice smooth, nice base layer with good grip']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 29.282695,
                    "list": "['making sure that all of that moisture is off of the hands', 'having an intentional attempt on the boulder problem']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 41.172164,
                    "list": "['climber placing their left foot on the hold', 'pivoting the left hip in immediately for the first move', 'going up with the left hand']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.095271,
                    "list": "[\"She's got her right foot keeping tension on the hold.\", 'Her left foot... is flagging, sticking into the wall, kind of providing a point of tension.', \"She's got three points of contact on holds and the fourth is keeping tension against the wall.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.374713,
                    "list": "['Flagging the left foot out in this position', 'Their hips are square to the wall', 'Opening up the legs wider', 'Use force from the right foot', 'Pivot right hip in', 'Reaching up overhand with their right hand']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 43.232293,
                    "list": "['Seems to save a bit of sequential energy']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 43.608927,
                    "list": "[\"she's starting in a straight arm position\", \"she seems like she's in a really good controlled state to be able to get to the first hand hold\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.097316,
                    "list": "[\"I do like how rigid her left foot looks. It's really posting into the wall.\", \"her left arm is pretty locked up, but it's kind of resting against her torso.\", \"she's twisting quite, and I can't see her right foot, but I would assume that her right foot is somewhat drop knee or drop to the side.\", \"her right foot is twisted into the wall, kind of knee up, right hip into the wall, left foot's posting.\", \"she's gonna be in a super stable platform to hit this first big hold that she's getting to.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 45.852272,
                    "list": "[\"She's now got her right hand up\", \"She's crossing that left foot high\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 45.966335,
                    "list": "['able to maintain core tension', 'cross through the plane of the body', 'securing a match on this big blue hold']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 46.428466,
                    "list": "[\"This step through is a good idea to be able to get weight in line with the hand that's hanging\", \"they'll be able to release their left hand and match on the next hold using less effort\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                }
            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 1.609394,
                    "list": "[\"Sometimes there's an excess of chalk built up by brushing the holds, kind of remove that layer of built-up chalk.\", \"By using this long brush, you'll be able to kind of get the holds up high that maybe are flat or slopier, pinchier, whatever she deems is maybe being tougher.\", \"By brushing them, she'll kind of get an extra edge by, you know, removing that layer of chalk and getting back to that, the friction of the hold, which should be easier to grip than chalky hands on top of a chalky hold.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 2.558072,
                    "list": "['An extended brush to get those higher holds.', 'Tends to be a lot of chalk buildup, skin oil buildup as the holds get dirty.', \"So it's really good to give him a nice brush, sort of clean them while you're in the midst of your attempts.\", \"I also made a mistake and didn't watch the full recording before annotating. So my bad, I'll watch it and go through it. Just got excited.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 20.311689,
                    "list": "['Make sure to take a few seconds to look at the route and memorize the sequence.', 'Shake out your hands to ensure that your arms feel loose and ready to climb.']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 23.309611,
                    "list": "[\"figure out what the movements are and what hands and what feet she's allowed to use\", 'create a better friction with her hands and the holds']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 41.172164,
                    "list": "['placing the left foot on the hold instead of the right foot']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.095271,
                    "list": "[\"Get those arms straight, really get to a spot where she's relaxed onto that foot, letting her power up completely from her lower body.\", \"What I'd like to see her do is relax her arms, kind of pull over onto her right foot more, keep her arms straight and kind of keep this left foot.\", 'Get this left foot a little straighter so that she can really drive through it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.374713,
                    "list": "['Allowing the climber to use force from the right foot', 'Pivoting the right hip in', 'Reaching up overhand with the right hand to reach the next hold']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 43.608927,
                    "list": "[\"I would argue that by doing this, she's forcing her right hand to go up first\", \"that could make it harder if she doesn't have good control of that flagging leg\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 45.852272,
                    "list": "['She needs to twist her body the opposite way', 'Instead of matching and having to do a bunch of foot matches while keeping your feet lower and slowly working up, she should keep tension on the next move']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 46.337642,
                    "list": "['Bring both feet over to the right side to maintain balance', 'Engage left hand more efficiently onto the handhold']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 46.428466,
                    "list": "[]",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.258715,
                    "list": "['Both of her feet are still out onto the right side over there but because of that her body weight is still falling to the left', \"There's no Flagging foot of hers or anything to help support her in this direction\", \"So because of that she's setting herself up to be completely off-balance\", \"And he's using a lot of arm strength and you can kind of tell because our arms are in a bent position right here\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.395888,
                    "list": "['She should have both arms relaxed and straight before moving her body up.', 'She needs to drive her force through her toes and over her feet for better balance and control.', 'She should avoid locking off her arms while trying to move her feet around.', 'She should focus on keeping tension with the lower body to avoid losing balance.']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.018249,
                    "list": "['Relax the arms and keep them straight', 'Let the lower body stay close to the wall', 'Get hips close to the wall to put pressure on toes']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.396462,
                    "list": "['The climber seems pretty gripped in this position and their right foot coming off created a windmill effect.', 'Getting feedback on the wall is proving to be difficult for the climber.', 'This ultimately results in a fall.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.588798,
                    "list": "[\"she's having a difficult time understanding what type of movement is required to climb efficiently and effectively\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.663099,
                    "list": "[\"There's a lack of engagement on the foothold when this cuts.\", 'The climber may be overly focused about keeping both hands on the hold, but they release tension on the foot inadvertently.', \"Now they're in a position where they're totally hanging on the upper body. This is a really tiring position to be in.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 51.244371,
                    "list": "['They may be hoping that they can use this position to get to the next hand hold as well', 'what would be more useful here is to get the left foot back down on a hold', 'They have a hold right in this range where they actually could stand on, shake out, and then make the next move before placing the heel']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 51.460443,
                    "list": "['Putting a heel hook at the same position where both of your hands are at usually is not the best thing to do right here because in this instance her body weight is now going directly down.', \"By forcing her body weight to go downwards that's even putting more strain on her arms because I would argue she's not getting any body weight released from the use of that heel hook.\", \"It seems like she's really struggling with this movement here and she's desperately trying to just throw up a heel hook to see if that will help her in this movement.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 51.539919,
                    "list": "['I think that this is the wrong wrong chance to do it.', 'So she cuts her feet and decides that the best possible move is to get her right foot as a match.', \"Now she's got all three points of contact that are anchoring here into the wall right here.\", \"There's no big solid platform base.\", \"Her you know, everything she's got is in a very, very small area.\", \"We're gonna make moving off this area very, very tough.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 51.94677,
                    "list": "[\"The climber just doesn't know quite what to do with their feet.\", 'They try to get this heel hook too early, making it impossible to generate out left.', 'The sequence of events is just off here. They got a little ahead of themselves.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 52.851446,
                    "list": "['She spent so much of the route locked off that her arms are just tired', 'Drive their lower body, use our bigger force, use our bigger muscles to drive ourselves up']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 54.356034,
                    "list": "['The climber should avoid backing down from the boulder and rather push themselves until failure to improve their skills.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_004_8"
                }
            ]
        },
