                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 175.629673,
                    "list": "['The pianist should make sure to play with the metronome to maintain a steady tempo.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 193.425684,
                    "list": "[\"This whole section starts to feel like it's rushing quite a bit, and the whole section doesn't feel like it makes a lot of musical sense. They should make sure that the rhythm is very stable so that it comes across as being a little bit more organized.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 263.332468,
                    "list": "['They can get into the key quicker and have a more efficient movement if they play with their fingertips.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 274.663988,
                    "list": "['They should try to isolate this section and just play it over and over again so they know exactly where their hand is supposed to go.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 284.286546,
                    "list": "['For it to come across even brighter, they can try to get quicker into the key and out of it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 301.874901,
                    "list": "['Both hands are playing quite fully so it starts to become a bit muddled.', 'The left hand should probably stay a little bit longer.', 'The right hand can be a little bit more articulate so that the balance works well.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 346.56271,
                    "list": "[\"The pianist is playing with flat fingers and often just hitting the keyboard with their hands. This isn't the most coordinated way to play. It often results in them feeling like they're rushing or they lose structure out of the piece.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 433.307853,
                    "list": "['They can still try to play more with their fingertips so that they can still get a rich sound, but also have a little bit more clarity and coordination.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 454.750534,
                    "list": "['They could be a little bit more efficient with this if they just kept their fingers on the keys instead of it coming in and out.']",
