                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 621.882785,
                    "list": "[\"This slowdown that they're doing should be a little bit more gradual, so it makes more sense.\", 'Right now, if you put a metronome to it, it would be very uneven.', 'It should still feel like it slows down progressively so that it feels natural.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 629.971348,
                    "list": "[\"All these fastnets don't seem to really link together and they're all a little bit too equal when playing. They should try to make sure that there's a longer phrase and that they play them lighter so it flows more.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 636.247078,
                    "list": "['Again, the coordination between the articulation here is not really working out.', 'This is mainly because they play with their flat fingers, so if they can have a little bit more coordination and be closer to the keys, their rhythm would be much improved.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 655.167865,
                    "list": "[\"The left hand and the right hand don't feel like they're always really working together.\", 'They should try to play very slowly and with a metronome so that they feel really, really coordinated.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 679.893549,
                    "list": "[\"The tempo that they're choosing to take always seems a little bit on the edge and starts to compress a bit.\", 'They should just make sure that they can practice it a little bit slowly and more accurately, and that would get the same energy that they want.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 705.717835,
                    "list": "['This run that they had in the right hand was really not that articulate.', \"They should try to make sure that when they're done playing chords, then they have more playing from their fingertips, and get closer to the keys for this type of faster playing.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 738.4549,
                    "list": "[\"The left hand starts to feel like it's rushing and pushing the right hand.\", \"They should make sure that they isolate just the left hand and put it within metronome so they really feel like they're grounded in the tempo.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 762.30168,
                    "list": "[\"Because of the tempo that they're taking and how their left hand feels like it's pushing a little bit, that led to some uncoordination there. They should make sure that they isolate both their hands so that they can practice very slowly.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0721_Piano_1_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 767.655679,
                    "list": "[\"They could try to get their fingers a little bit closer together so that it's more efficient and without any fatigue.\"]",
