            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 25.335274,
                    "list": "[\"You could also use a chef's knife.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 38.806789,
                    "list": "['I would like to see him go ahead and directly throw this excess garbage away.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 41.093074,
                    "list": "[\"You don't want that to be included in your dish\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.765133,
                    "list": "['He needs to have better position for his fingers.', 'Fingertips way too close to the blade.', 'He needs to tuck him a little.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 55.581694,
                    "list": "['the uniformity helps things cook more evenly and come out cooked at the same time']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 76.356147,
                    "list": "[\"When making a classic omelet you're filling, in this case the onions and the chili, should be sauteed prior to adding them to the omelet.\", 'This can be done using the same pan that the omelet will be cooked in, just removing the cooked veg from the pan prior to cooking the eggs.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 82.634006,
                    "list": "['It appears to be about a fourth of a teaspoon.', 'I believe that he should do this step after adding the egg to the bowl. However, they could be done in this manner.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 102.732092,
                    "list": "['You could also just crack the egg on the edge of the mixing bowl or on the countertop']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.914351,
                    "list": "['put the egg shell directly into the garbage']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 113.98823,
                    "list": "['The eggs you should be using two to three eggs to make a proper omelet.', 'An alternative to the fork would be a whisk.', 'What you want to prevent is any white streaks of the egg in your end omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 130.485339,
                    "list": "['Use a more professional and appropriate language when describing the cooking process.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 130.783815,
                    "list": "['This pan is a little too large in diameter for the egg that is going to be cooked.', 'A better choice is a six to eight inch diameter or 15 to 20 centimeter diameter saute pan.', \"The flame is being lit under the pan and it's a relatively large flame.\", 'I would recommend using a low flame because what we want to do is prevent the egg from any browning.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 149.78011,
                    "list": "['A classic omelet is traditionally made with clarified butter.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 152.471261,
                    "list": "['Add the oil more carefully to avoid splattering.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 155.592487,
                    "list": "[\"Here I would like to see him use a measuring spoon so he knows exactly how much oil he's adding.\", \"However it's always better to measure your ingredients so you know exactly how much you're using.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 160.993869,
                    "list": "['This is so that when he adds the omelet to the pan, he can ensure that it will not stick. Alternates to using oil would be butter or pan spray.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 177.832959,
                    "list": "[\"He's looking to form a base before he tries to flip it.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 180.84248,
                    "list": "['His pan is a larger diameter than the volume of his egg mixture. He should use a smaller pan to achieve a better shape.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 181.265016,
                    "list": "['This is an indication that the heat is too high. So to avoid this sizzling, start with a low flame rather than a high flame for cooking the egg.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 182.297104,
                    "list": "['the oil is very hot and is going to make his omelet cook at a rapid pace']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 189.287979,
                    "list": "['He should tilt the pan a little bit more to ensure even cooking of the entire mixture.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 189.756351,
                    "list": "[\"He would be better served by spreading this mixture out so that it's all one layer.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 191.30324,
                    "list": "['This would indicate that there was too much oil used in the pan and will result in a very oily end product.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 196.261318,
                    "list": "['Holding the omelet against the side with the spatula is not a very standard technique for making an omelet. It would be easier to scrape into the unoccupied parts of the pan instead of using a sliding action.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 205.034756,
                    "list": "[\"He's got a little softness in the middle so he wants to keep moving it\", 'so he can flip it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 206.637713,
                    "list": "[\"Don't put too much pressure on any one part of the omelet\", 'Avoid pressing against the sides with the spatula']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 218.40708,
                    "list": "['that would never have been flipped']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 223.027537,
                    "list": "['When making a classic omelet, one would not want to flip the egg over.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 231.005,
                    "list": "['Pressing with spatula deflates air bubbles', 'Pressing makes egg mixture more dense', \"Don't press on it to make it cook faster\", \"It doesn't take very long to cook all the way through\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 241.723805,
                    "list": "['Again, a lower heat and no flipping will help to minimize or eliminate any browning.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 254.737502,
                    "list": "['Transferring the omelet from the hot griddle pan to your plate can be challenging. Here are some tips to improve your skill in this step:']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 255.872535,
                    "list": "[\"Placing the plate on the burner that's not being used is not recommended. It can cause confusion and accidents in the kitchen. It's important to keep the workspace organized and only use the necessary burners for cooking.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 260.499435,
                    "list": "['The omelet has been flipped several times prior to folding in half.', 'The omelet is quite overcooked due to the browning on the exterior.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 266.031179,
                    "list": "[\"he's pressing on it, which again, I would not do.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 268.242913,
                    "list": "['The preparer should avoid repeatedly flipping the folded omelet and pressing down on it with the wooden spatula. This creates an overcooked and tough end product.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 273.6155,
                    "list": "['Somewhat overcooked']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_59_2"
                }
            ]
        },
