            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 2.747323,
                    "list": "['I would love to see the shooter just more of a basketball position, I would say, or stance.', \"Like you're waiting for this pass in a game or in this drill, have your knees bent, drop your hips, really meet this pass.\", \"Let's catch it with our right hand and let's backstop it so we can just catch and shoot it.\", \"If you catch it with your left and you're a right hand shooter, then you're going to move it to your right and it just takes seconds and seconds mean you're going to be defended.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 3.50968,
                    "list": "['have his body placement position lower in an athletic stance', 'become quicker going into his release', 'more unbalanced', 'more powerful going into his jump', 'allowing the ball to gain the proper rotation, arc, and accuracy']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 4.268333,
                    "list": "['moving the guide hand elbow in so that forearm is parallel to the floor', 'making sure the palm of the guide hand is facing inward', 'landing on both feet for better balance']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 4.50829,
                    "list": "['we will want the player looking on the right side of the frame to keep his follow through extended above his shoulder after the release', 'allowing the ball to gain more momentum, arc and accuracy it needs to develop the proper angle of dropping inside the rim.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 5.215767,
                    "list": "['did not develop that proper arc and rotation', \"player's body's momentum bringing him backwards\", 'follow through not being extended above his shoulder']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 8.497906,
                    "list": "[\"we will want to move the players elbow just inside of his body's frame to allow it to create a better alignment of directing the ball after the release\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 8.793923,
                    "list": "[\"Again, even his takeoff, he's just kind of pushing off the left foot and the right leg just kind of goes up. He's just kind of, I don't know, like one leg in it, if you will. I'm not sure what to even call it, but you're a little off balance. You're not, you know, maybe as balanced as you need to be to finish, but you know, he's got a beautiful, beautiful, beautiful follow through. Again, let's move that guide hand in a little bit.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 8.879895,
                    "list": "['He should be a little more stable with his base here. You see how he has that right foot kind of flared out.']",
                    "expert_uid": "500w0s",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 9.200381,
                    "list": "[\"Let's hold that follow through.\", \"Let's absorb the shock of coming down by coming on our balls of our feet.\", 'Bending our knees, dropping our hips a little bit.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-16-23_01_30"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 14.329498,
                    "list": "[\"let's extend that shooting elbow maybe a little bit more\"]",
