                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 37.320169,
                    "list": "['encourage him to flag his left foot higher up into the wall', 'with some good intention of being pressed up into the wall', 'get even more power generated onto that right foot to help with this move']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 41.770519,
                    "list": "['His back is kind of rounding, so he needs to keep himself in there.', 'He needs to get his hips closer to the wall.']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.005137,
                    "list": "[\"I wouldn't encourage it for the majority of climbers right here because as you can tell in the third person image right here, even though he has his legs in a bent position right here and his arm is relatively straight, a lot of his body weight is being pulled straight down underneath right here.\", \"And I would say that there's not too much body weight being used on his legs right now, so the majority of the body weight he's experiencing right now is actually on his right arm.\", 'So in the future I would probably not encourage your feet to go up too high like this because you can kind of see his hips are sitting really low to the ground which is just pulling him away from the wall at this point.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.018296,
                    "list": "['Usually in a case like this, you would want to be biking where one foot presses down and the other foot presses up.', 'So you kind of get this pinching effect with your toes.', 'Usually you still want to be opposite opposed for the most part.', 'So this seems a little bit interesting.', 'It seems like it could work.', \"It's definitely making him scrunch and you can see he's got the really high feet but his butt and his hips are kind of staying out away from the wall.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 43.87204,
                    "list": "[\"I think that with how far the hips are down here, this isn't the most effective way that one could climb this boulder.\", 'I think that there are probably some foot options a little bit lower that would have made this move a little bit easier.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.878106,
                    "list": "[\"I don't know if it was the smoothest way\", 'he readjusts the left foot', \"If he's executing correctly, you know, the heel drives down, the foot drives in, and then the foot kind of drives along the wall\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 47.741781,
                    "list": "['he can bring his left hand to the next handhold']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.614344,
                    "list": "['So the further left or right your foot is from your body, the better']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_21"
                },
