            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 53.533877,
                    "list": "['When playing with their left hand, you can see that their fingers are getting really high up off the string. To be the most efficient, they should try to keep them as close to the string.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 59.959532,
                    "list": "[\"These notes that they're playing are a bit out of tune. They can try playing with a tuner, or they can play these notes and play with an open string to get more context about the intonation.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 62.558292,
                    "list": "['The violinist is using a small amount of bow and not much weight to create this very light sound.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 101.899478,
                    "list": "['To get a lighter sound, play with the tip of the bow.', 'To get more articulation, pronate more with your right hand and put more weight into your first finger.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 127.289563,
                    "list": "['These single notes could be more compact using less bow.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 139.421733,
                    "list": "['so that they could play more at the frog of the bow.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 170.1399,
                    "list": "['They could just slightly speed it up a little bit more so both the strings sound better.', \"There's more resistance in the bow since they're playing two strings.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 188.17091,
                    "list": "['They should overall have a very curved thumb with a very soft touch contact with the frog.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 211.711026,
                    "list": "['Their left hand should have a more efficient position with fingers closer to the fingerboard.']",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 224.684676,
                    "list": "[\"Sometimes it's appropriate, but during this section I feel like they could use more of their lower amount of bow, closer to the frog.\", \"They're not utilizing their upper arm. They can bring it closer to their body to help get closer to the frog.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 244.197462,
                    "list": "['The participant is not utilizing this part of the bow.', \"They're not bringing in their upper arm enough to be able to get close to that section.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 257.656465,
                    "list": "[\"Again, you can see how far your fingers are going away from the fingerboard. It's best, even if they're not playing them, to try to keep it as close as possible to be as efficient as possible.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 267.231004,
                    "list": "['They could be even more efficient and have clear string crossings if they make more use of opening up their elbow.', \"So the string crossings come from just opening up the elbow as they're playing.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "tja8o9",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0726_Duet_Violin_1_1_2"
