                {
                    "video_time": 48.322959,
                    "list": "['His knee is slightly twisting in.', 'He could push through a little bit more.', 'Bringing his forearm and bicep to his chest would help him reach further.', 'He should stand straight through one limb and really drive through the feet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 50.113162,
                    "list": "['he could kind of Set the heel lower', 'maybe having a heel hook would have been better']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 50.601303,
                    "list": "['using a pretty slow pace']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 54.948085,
                    "list": "['his left arm is slightly bent here because it is in an undercling hold', 'you kind of have to pull yourself into the wall as well with your arm to make sure that you can come out of that undercling']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 54.964157,
                    "list": "[\"He doesn't really ever fully commit to straightening his right leg out on these moves. He kind of only partially bends it.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 59.115252,
                    "list": "['The climber is taking a lot of time to find the best foot.', \"If you're naturally bent towards being a climber with good endurance, taking your time is a good tactic.\", \"This climber is choosing to take their time and really make sure they're making the right decision.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 61.650539,
                    "list": "['Spending less time looking around for his feet', 'Avoiding cutting his feet to move them, as it adds strain on his arms']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 61.736053,
                    "list": "['The climber should minimize hesitancy and make quicker decisions.', 'They should aim to establish themselves into the next position sooner.', 'They should conserve energy by not staying on suboptimal handholds for too long.']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 63.356123,
                    "list": "[\"one thing about this position is it doesn't actually cause him to be unbalanced\", 'what this climber does in order to compensate for that balance is he flags his left foot down and to the right', 'by placing it down and to the right it helps to gain control of his body weight', \"helps to stop that momentum so his body doesn't rotate out to the right\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 69.163702,
                    "list": "['And that beta previously with the back flag really set them up to be able to move into this right hand a lot more effectively without any foot switching.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 69.390757,
                    "list": "['put their foot in this range as much as possible', 'higher the foot is up into the left pressing']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 74.440867,
                    "list": "['The climber should try to be more efficient in their decision-making process. Instead of just looking around and searching for the right foot placement, they should already have a plan of where to place their foot before initiating the campus move.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 74.995158,
                    "list": "['Instead of cutting his feet free and jumping up, he should try to walk his feet up to conserve energy.']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 77.740488,
                    "list": "['the climber can improve by being less reliant on the right hand for upward force.', 'the climber should work on maintaining better body position to alleviate tension on the right hand.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 81.33958,
                    "list": "['In order to get his body weight on his right foot, he would probably have to straighten out his arms to ensure that the majority of his body weight gets placed on his legs.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2z4v0b",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 81.573617,
                    "list": "[\"He's not really getting into a better position\", \"He's staying locked off and high on these holes\", 'Instead of kind of sinking into this right hand and kind of leaning off the side and kind of finding that optimal position with his arms straight', 'He kind of just stays high and attempts to bump out and just unfortunately not enough']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 82.187318,
                    "list": "['they spend quite a bit of time gazing down and left trying to find that better foothold', \"the higher foothold is very high and I don't think they even look towards that position\", \"they could then bump the left hand into either of the gas stones and it's now a side pole\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 82.289681,
                    "list": "['Unable to target the hold, should work on accuracy and precision']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_019_6"
                }
            ]
        },
