                    "list": "['good job kicking his foot out', 'nice footwork right on the music', 'really good eye contact to the audience']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                }
            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 19.210589,
                    "list": "['he is flat on his feet', 'go up on his toes', 'bend those knees', 'have a little more roundedness to the floor']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 19.676406,
                    "list": "['He should bend his knees a little bit more and keep his movement smaller and more tightly underneath him.', 'He should get control of his pelvis and engage his arms to have more stability and ability to move quickly.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 31.483861,
                    "list": "[\"if this back foot was the toe was up, he'd be it'll be a lot easier for him to change position\", \"So stepping full with the full foot on the front foot right now it's the right and then just having the toe up for the back leg\", \"So you're able to shift your weight a lot easier and you're able to go faster because you're shifting your weight correctly\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 31.950751,
                    "list": "['He struggles to transition from the quickness of the kicks prior to this into the more grounded movement here.', 'It would benefit him to bend his knees more significantly and drop his pelvis back to be more grounded.', 'Keep his movements smaller and tighter underneath him.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 36.913724,
                    "list": "['I think if this were advanced choreography the dancer probably could squat all the way down in time and get up.']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.521582,
                    "list": "['getting more of the rhythmic embodiment', 'maintaining the bend in the knees and dropping back of the pelvis']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.919688,
                    "list": "['jump back to help with the timing', 'get up on his toes when he goes back']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 57.98243,
                    "list": "['His upper body could do a little bit of something, have some kind of movement.', 'Maybe pushing his hands out, pushing them up, or just swinging them down closer to his waist by his side.']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 62.757418,
                    "list": "['He struggles to perform this kind of larger movement.', 'He really disconnects from any rhythmic embodiment he had had thus far.', 'He struggles to keep up with the tempo and the music while performing this bigger step.', 'It would help him here to move quickly and make his steps a lot smaller to minimize the amount of movement he needs to do in a short time period.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 71.116212,
                    "list": "[\"he's just a bit all over the place\", 'counting would definitely help', 'thinking about which direction you want to face', \"staying in that direction until you're at a good point in the music or the song\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 86.826694,
                    "list": "['slowing down and going to more of the melody of the music', 'not always dancing to the fast beats', 'taking his time and controlling his body', 'giving the dance better structure']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 98.816966,
                    "list": "['It would benefit him to take smaller movements, smaller kicks, smaller jumps,', 'incorporate his arms more fully so he can use his entire body', 'not only connect to the rhythm but also to keep him from getting fatigued.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.031094,
                    "list": "['He really starts to lose any sort of specificity in his movements.', 'He kind of flicks his legs outwards performing the kick.', 'While holding his arms very loosely by his sides, he has a bouncing quality to his movement, which is really disconnecting him from the rhythm and keeping him from being able to move quickly and efficiently.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 111.829885,
                    "list": "['I think less is sometimes more.', \"Maybe take out the bounces and then he'll be able to better do the steps on the right beat.\", \"But the extra bounce isn't really necessary.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_4_4"
                }
            ]
