                {
                    "video_time": 86.342622,
                    "list": "['The dancer should work on incorporating more variety in their steps and movements.']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 88.255524,
                    "list": "['When she transitioned from the left side to the right side she kind of missed a step because when she stepped her foot out she took a double step instead of just stepping on the foot to switch sides.', \"thinking about your weight shifting whenever you want to change feet whatever foot you're changing to it should be the leg that the weight is not on so that way you can easily transfer your weight to the other side\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 88.558722,
                    "list": "['When the dancer switches to the other side, they almost lose their balance.', 'Making sure they are staying on their toes.', 'Staying balanced when they transition from one step to another, which was not as smooth as it could be.']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 90.355619,
                    "list": "['She should work on making her upper body or arm movements here more precise so we can see what the choreography actually is.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 90.406318,
                    "list": "['The dancer needs to understand the rhythm.', 'This lacks musicality.', 'Movements are not flowing with the rhythm or the music.', 'The dancer should embody the music and become the music.', 'The dancer is off with the rhythm.', \"The step touches at the beginning don't match the rhythm of the music.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 91.33336,
                    "list": "['To improve this movement, I would question where is the body movement in the arms initiating from?', 'Is it the palm of hands making the shoulders react to it, or is it the shoulders moving that causes the arm to react?', 'So being very clear on what the arms are, or is it all together that the arms are kind of free flowing to whatever the feet are doing?', \"Right now it's not clear because it seems as if the dancer is alternating where the emphasis of the movement is.\", 'So creating some clarity in this would be very helpful.']",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 93.244915,
                    "list": "['She has to really concentrate on the levels of her arms', \"Whether they're supposed to be both hands at the same level or the same height in space\", 'One arm is supposed to be higher and one is supposed to be lower']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 95.361986,
                    "list": "['Her gaze is fairly low and inconsistent throughout, which demonstrates a lack of confidence.', 'She tends to lose the rhythm in some moments, specifically through the use of her arms and her upper body.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 95.975585,
                    "list": "['The dancer needs to work on her flexibility in her wrists.', 'The movement would be better executed if her wrists were flexed to create a 90 degree angle with her arm.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 97.371886,
                    "list": "['step and then touch the top of the toe or the toe from side to side']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 98.728628,
                    "list": "['The dancer needs to show a stark difference between her steps by making it clearer when she crosses behind. She should cross the foot further back so that we can see the difference compared to the step touch.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 101.250369,
                    "list": "['The participant should work on keeping their arms more controlled and synchronized with their body movements.']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 101.867149,
                    "list": "['She can work on varying her steps instead of repeating step touch']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 108.238933,
                    "list": "['She should count out and pay attention to the beat of the music to line up her steps better with the music.']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.169382,
                    "list": "['The dancer should verbally say the rhythm to themselves before performing.', \"They should be able to articulate the rhythm they want to achieve, for example 'body body body ba ba', before actually doing the step.\", 'They should understand not only the rhythm of the music but also the rhythm of the steps.']",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.922702,
                    "list": "['She should shuffle her foot across the floor, making contact with the floor when her foot goes forward and when it goes backwards.', \"She is kicking her foot too high off the ground, resulting in no audible sound when it should make a 'boom boom' sound.\", 'She should ensure that her foot remains in contact with the floor throughout the shuffle.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.922702,
                    "list": "['The part of her foot that should be making that shuffle sound...is the bottom of her foot, the ball of her foot...That is the part of her foot that should be making contact with the floor.', 'And only the ball of her foot, the tippy toe portion of her foot, the underside bottom should be making contact with the floor.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 110.248866,
                    "list": "['lacking consistency in this movement', 'disconnected from the rhythm', \"times where she's disconnected from the rhythm appear a little bit more awkward\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
