                },
                {
                    "video_time": 143.631765,
                    "list": "['to dance through the fingertips', 'extend the energy all the way out through their fingertips', 'follow through with their fingertips']",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 144.671562,
                    "list": "[\"It's not really clear where her arms should be in this movement.\", 'She needs some specificity in her upper body, whether her arms should be bent, whether her arms should be straight.', \"And especially it's lacking some energy.\", \"So the step would be better if she did really straighten her arms each time she's reaching out, her energy would radiate from her upper body outward into the space, outward to the audience, outward to whoever is watching.\", 'And that would be much better.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 147.314584,
                    "list": "['Each area of negative space between her fingers should be the same.', \"It's important that her hands are a jazz hand and her fingers are equidistantly spread.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 147.31583,
                    "list": "['make sure that heel is off the floor and it stays glued to the floor']",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 148.170188,
                    "list": "['She could benefit from some clarity in this arm shape.', 'Her arms are quite unclear, they have a slight bend to them, but not too much of a purposeful bend.', \"They're a little bit disconnected from the rhythm here as well.\", 'Overall, some clarity in the shape of her upper body would really be beneficial.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 152.759006,
                    "list": "[\"The dancer's sternum and chest is a little bit awkward here.\", 'She is not designating space over here where her shoulders are.', 'Her shoulders, even if her arm is up, which right here, her left arm is pointing upward, even so some oppositional forces should be in play in that her shoulders specifically should be pointing downward or like gravity is be taking them further down.', 'Even if her arm is pressing up, her arm would actually look higher up if her shoulders were pressed down, it would create some space for that movement to be fully seen.', 'It would make her arm longer because her shoulder being pressed down, which is accentuate how high her arm actually is.', \"If her shoulder is up, her arm isn't actually gonna get any higher and it's gonna look a bit crunched instead of elongated and it should look elongated.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 152.759006,
                    "list": "['Her fingers are kind of stiff here.', 'That is not the way the hand is supposed to be.', \"Her middle finger looks like it's pressed downwards and her thumb is flared out.\", 'Either her hands should be in a jazz hand, all fingers equidistant, or her hands should be in a blade, meaning that all the fingers are tucked in together.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 152.944013,
                    "list": "[\"They could definitely hold that pose for a little longer to give more emphasis to the actual pose that they're doing\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 160.150416,
                    "list": "['She could benefit from some clarity in her upper body.', 'She could benefit from some more direct movement and getting her arms straight out with more energy and power.', 'She should avoid flicking her arms with an indirect quality.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 161.966054,
                    "list": "['I think she could have come down further this way', 'or come down in this direction and really made that a nice little around the world moment in that space and made it even bigger', \"Because the music has changed, it's now you hear the horns a little bit more, so you want your body to match the music a little more.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 161.995375,
                    "list": "[\"if they only use their legs, it wouldn't add as much depth to their movement\", \"they can't travel as much around the space\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "a44vde",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 162.785537,
                    "list": "['The dancer should improve the pathway of her arm', 'She should make her arm movement more linear instead of in an arc', 'Her arm should go straight out when her elbow is straightened']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 163.672169,
                    "list": "['have a command over all of her movement', 'her whole body can be strong and direct and energetic']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 164.194415,
                    "list": "['Encourage them to use their torso and engage it throughout the dance.', 'Emphasize the need for the torso to lift and reach in coordination with the arm movements.', 'Ensure that the torso is not sliding away from the body, but rather pulling in the opposite direction.', 'Explain that activating the torso will improve the overall look, lines, and dimension of the dance.']",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 165.48321,
                    "list": "[\"We're not on the rhythm\", \"We're either half a second ahead or half a second behind\", \"We're delayed with the music\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 167.414218,
                    "list": "[\"Overall, it looks like she's marking this step slightly, not executing it fully.\", 'Heightened energy, more specific movement, and more direct movement of the limbs would really benefit her here.']",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 172.625841,
                    "list": "['She could benefit from a better posture happening through the arms and the legs and particularly the torso.', \"This leg straightens but doesn't fully straighten at the knee. She could really benefit from straightening at that knee more and also creating a more definitive shape with the foot.\", 'If she were to flex or point that foot, it would benefit her.', \"Her other supporting leg is also in a bit of an awkward position. It's turned in slightly with the foot turned out, which is creating this awkward line of energy between the two feet where she's not able to support the kick as well as she might have if she were to turn this other leg out and bend that knee more deeply.\", \"Her torso is twisting in a bit of an awkward way, which doesn't really support this kick. As she were to align her torso a bit more clearly where her shoulders are on top of her hips, she would open up range of movement in this kicking leg, allowing her to kick much higher than she is right now.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "mg5x5a",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 173.103848,
                    "list": "[\"She doesn't allow herself to reach her full potential because she doesn't straighten her leg all the way.\", \"The movement is smaller than it could have been if she accentuates the movement all the way out to the tips of her toes and doesn't hold back or cut back that line.\", 'She just needs to really move her energy out then back in, but definitely make sure that it does get out.']",
                    "expert_uid": "pc14sf",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 175.129655,
                    "list": "['it would be really important that the teacher dancer is counting out those steps because it is hard to kind of figure out the timing and the steps together.']",
