                },
                {
                    "video_time": 211.217378,
                    "list": "['To improve this section of the dance, I would question if the dance is supposed to be more melodic, which the music sounds currently at this moment, or is it supposed to be while the music is melodic, the dancer kind of has, creates like these striking rhythms in it, right?', \"If it's supposed to be more melodic, I would encourage the dancer to have more flow and be a little bit more graceful as they move. And they can do this by swinging their arms and being more gentle in their body.\", \"Or if it's supposed to be striking, as opposed to the music being more melodic, to have more power and precision in this whole phrase work here.\", \"So it's choreographic choice.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "r2u6t3",
                    "video_name": "upenn_0713_Dance_5_6"
                },
