                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 45.143074,
                    "list": "['Dropping the right foot and transitioning weight increases stability', 'Opposing the weight being pulled down by pulling to the right with the left heel']",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 46.193967,
                    "list": "[\"He doesn't transfer his self out of the heel hook that well.\", \"You can see he's actually cutting his feet and so now all of his weight is now on his left and right arm.\", 'This would probably be a good spot to like you know bring the right foot over, switch the left heel onto this hold, switch the left heel to a toe and then be able to push and drive out instead of cutting your feet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.397776,
                    "list": "[\"He's gonna really want to drive that knee over that foot\", \"that's gonna let him take as much weight off his hands as possible\"]",
