                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                }
            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 1.689658,
                    "list": "[\"I'd love to see this off hand be up a little bit more to add some protection to the ball.\", 'You want it up more, ready to catch the ball and to go into your shot.', \"He's a little upright. I'd love to see him bent down, knees bent a little bit more.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 2.722359,
                    "list": "['Ball placement is kind of low.', 'You want to be able to have that ball high and tight around your chest area to explode up going into your layup.', 'So just understanding going into the layup, you want to have it a little bit higher and a little bit tighter so you can explode up and go off the backboard for the layup.']",
                    "expert_uid": "ec8x25",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 2.779589,
                    "list": "['we will want to bring the ball placement position higher towards his shoulders area', 'help create more security on the ball before his finish', 'help establish protection and a shield from the defender']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 2.779589,
                    "list": "['not have the player take off so late', 'If the player takes off a step earlier, he will have more room to operate and will be less likely to find himself under the rim']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 3.197883,
                    "list": "['left foot should be higher', 'right foot should be driving for more power']",
                    "expert_uid": "500w0s",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 11.676352,
                    "list": "['he was a little long on the backboard']",
                    "expert_uid": "500w0s",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 14.791956,
                    "list": "['Player should lower their body position for better balance, power, and explosiveness on the drive towards the rim.', 'Lowering the body position will help prevent defenders from knocking the player off balance while initiating contact.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 16.072178,
                    "list": "['the offensive player did not give the ball the right amount of spin to be able to hit our targeted area, which is the right corner, top right corner of the box on the backboard', \"the ball's target is on the top of the backboard, which does not give it the proper angle it needs to drop through the rim\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 16.19947,
                    "list": "['You need to put spin on this ball to get it in', 'maybe not the experience and repetitions to kind of possess the touch and skill to make this layup consistently']",
                    "expert_uid": "500w0s",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 24.222163,
                    "list": "['hope to see more consistency for the rest of this video']",
                    "expert_uid": "500w0s",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 27.921476,
                    "list": "['To get a better motion, I think he could start a little bit further out in order to give himself a more realistic approach.', 'taking one to four steps and going into the layup.']",
                    "expert_uid": "ec8x25",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 29.733271,
                    "list": "['he may come down a little bit to under the basket', \"you'd like for him to kind of be out in here a little bit\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.045175,
                    "list": "['I think the overall speed could highly be improved.', 'So just being able to pick up the speed, pick up the pace to get a better, better look at this is definitely is a helpful point to improve the consistency of the layout.']",
                    "expert_uid": "ec8x25",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.521899,
                    "list": "['I would love to see him square his shoulders up', 'maybe bring the right shoulder around a little bit', 'get that shooting hand behind the ball']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.648333,
                    "list": "['would love that one dribble to be more of a power dribble with a little authority to help give yourself momentum to create this opportunity.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.830104,
                    "list": "['Bring the ball placement position to be higher above his shoulders', 'Prevent the defense from having an easy access of stripping the ball', 'Help the player finish more efficiently by having the ball placement position closer towards the rim compared to it being lower towards the ground']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.700343,
                    "list": "['However, we can notice that the ball hits more towards the middle of the box, not allowing it to get the proper angle it needs to be able to drop through the net.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.706609,
                    "list": "['The ball landed more towards the middle area of the box, not allowing it the proper angle to be able to drop through the net.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 55.368271,
                    "list": "['We will want to bring the ball placement position higher towards his shoulders', 'to prevent exposing the ball to the defense', 'to allow them an opportunity of stripping the ball and causing an offensive turnover for the player.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 56.695958,
                    "list": "['Ball placement on the layup was on the top right side, which resulted to a miss on the layup.', \"So if you don't throw the ball a little bit over to the right, take some spin off.\", \"If you're going to bring it over to the right, make sure you put the right amount of spin on.\", \"Understanding the dynamic of the spin and understand the dynamic of where you hit the bag more and make sure it's a good combination.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "ec8x25",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 62.503427,
                    "list": "['That is the target.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 63.618678,
                    "list": "['he could get to the 8 range with increased effort and just overall aggressiveness in the layup', 'more game-like effort']",
                    "expert_uid": "500w0s",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_15"
                }
            ]
