        {
            "task_id": 1001,
            "task_name": "Cooking an Omelet",
            "scenario_name": "Cooking",
            "university_id": "ego4d-iiith",
            "origin_participant_id": "P0030",
            "take_uid": "26065a7c-c2dc-475d-acff-6b5b9cb94469",
            "video_paths": {
                "ego": "takes/iiith_cooking_89_2/frame_aligned_videos/aria01_214-1.mp4",
                "exo1": "takes/iiith_cooking_89_2/frame_aligned_videos/cam01.mp4",
                "exo2": "takes/iiith_cooking_89_2/frame_aligned_videos/cam02.mp4",
                "exo3": "takes/iiith_cooking_89_2/frame_aligned_videos/cam03.mp4",
                "exo4": "takes/iiith_cooking_89_2/frame_aligned_videos/cam04.mp4"
            },
            "good_executions": [
                {
                    "video_time": 119.386295,
                    "list": "[\"Here's some green chili has been cut up and added to the small metal bowl with the onions and the seasonings.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 174.070966,
                    "list": "['the egg has been added to the small metal bowl', 'is being mixed with a spoon']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 227.340851,
                    "list": "['the egg is being spread into a very thin layer', 'allow or will better allow the mixing of the egg using a rubber spatula to form those soft curds']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                }
            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 10.181363,
                    "list": "['The preparer should use a saute pan that is between 6 to 8 inches in diameter with sides of 1 1\u20442 to 2 inches tall instead of a larger diameter pan.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 16.930785,
                    "list": "['The pan has been placed on a lit burner before preparing the omelet ingredients. This can result in the pan being too hot and causing the egg to overcook quickly.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.900739,
                    "list": "['The preparer has selected a metal spatula for the preparation of the omelet. The tool that is typically used would be a rubber spatula so that once the egg is added to the pan, it can be gently stirred with the rubber spatula until curds of the egg form.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 53.89313,
                    "list": "['Based on individual tastes, other seasonings and spices can be utilized.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 102.02197,
                    "list": "['Typically, vegetables used for a filling on an omelet would be saut\u00e9ed first and then removed from the saut\u00e9 pan. After the vegetables were cooked, then the omelet itself would be made and the vegetables added in at the end.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 119.386295,
                    "list": "['Again, this would typically be sauteed prior to making the omelet and then added in at the end of making the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 148.522488,
                    "list": "['Oil should not be added to the egg prior to cooking.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 174.070966,
                    "list": "['the egg be the first thing to be placed in the bowl', 'either a fork or a whisk or chopsticks be used to whisk the egg really well', 'trying to accomplish a homogeneous mixture']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 208.928153,
                    "list": "['The typical fat used for making an omelet is clarified butter.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 216.730863,
                    "list": "['The pan is too hot.', 'Use low to medium-low heat when making an omelet.', 'Slowly cook the egg and form nice curds while stirring.', 'Allow the omelet to cook on low heat to prevent browning of the exterior.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 227.340851,
                    "list": "['a smaller diameter saute pan will allow or will better allow the mixing of the egg using a rubber spatula to form those soft curds']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 241.411793,
                    "list": "['additional oil has been added to the pan along the edges of the omelet', \"it's really not necessary to add additional oil\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 265.412058,
                    "list": "['With a classic omelet there is no flipping of the omelet.', 'It is allowed to cook in place in the saut\u00e9 pan once those curds have formed.', \"You can also notice browning on the exterior of the omelet which is something that you're trying to avoid with a classic omelet.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 272.648658,
                    "list": "['Lighting the flame after it has gone out is unnecessary as the egg is already finished cooking.', 'Ensure that there is enough liquid in the omelet before flipping it to prevent it from becoming dry and overcooked.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 321.07029,
                    "list": "['The omelet is removed from the pan and remains flat.', 'A typical omelet would be either folded in half or rolled.', \"If you're folding the omelet in half, your filling would go on half of the omelet and the other half folded over the filling.\", \"If you're rolling an omelet, you're going to roll the omelet and place it onto a serving plate.\", 'Cut a small cut in the top of the omelet about three inches long in the middle of the top, and your filling would be added into that slit that you made.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_89_2"
                }
            ]
        },
