            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 8.477624,
                    "list": "['The participant should be careful when choosing and gathering their ingredients to ensure they are fresh and of high quality.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 14.427403,
                    "list": "[\"I typically recommend when making a raw salad to use a plastic cutting board. It just is easier to clean. It doesn't hold as much bacteria or smells.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 21.239,
                    "list": "[\"A better selection here would be a chef's knife, which would give the user a bit more control.\", \"It's always important to ensure that any knife used is very, very sharp.\", 'Failure to use a sharp knife can result in the knife slipping while cutting, especially through something like tomato skin, and result in cutting the individual using the knife.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 24.838581,
                    "list": "[]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 26.83755,
                    "list": "['He should aim for more precise cutting and try to maintain consistent thickness throughout the cucumber slices.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 29.229003,
                    "list": "['I would actually recommend if he was only going to use partial of the cucumber to cut it in half lengthwise.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 29.540388,
                    "list": "[\"It's very challenging to peel things that are this small.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 31.482043,
                    "list": "[\"It's pale in its cucumber right now.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.355085,
                    "list": "['he has a little bit of trouble with it because the piece is so small', \"as he's removed that skin, the cucumber itself is wet\", 'So that makes it just harder to hold']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.921576,
                    "list": "['he kind of struggles to peel the skin off of this very short one and a half inch round', 'I would recommend that he cut in half lengthwise on the longer piece if he was going to only choose to use half of it']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.838703,
                    "list": "['A better practice would be to have a small bowl or container that you could put all your cooking scraps into as you go along keeping a neater, tidier kitchen.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.990009,
                    "list": "[\"I would recommend using more of the cucumber or peeling it with the cucumber hole and then cutting your piece off of the peeled section just because it gives you more leverage and you'll have more surface area to work with.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 51.194781,
                    "list": "[\"make a flat side for any cuts you're making so that it doesn't roll away while you're trying to cut it\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 56.515459,
                    "list": "['He probably could have just cut it in half once and then use those flat sides to make his next cuts.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 56.845591,
                    "list": "[\"It's not a very chef-driven method or technique to his cuts.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 73.016369,
                    "list": "[\"Now he's cut the end off of the tomato where the stem would attach. You don't want that in your food. It's hard and doesn't taste good.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 85.545801,
                    "list": "['You always want to have a clean serving piece']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 119.966097,
                    "list": "['In addition to these two ingredients, salt would be an excellent addition.', 'In addition to balance the oil, an acid such as lemon juice or red wine vinegar should be added just to enhance the flavor.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 123.581454,
                    "list": "['He has skipped two key ingredients in this recipe, which is an acid and salt.', 'Salt is necessary for rounding out the flavor of the salad and acid is a necessary component as well.', 'For the salad, you could use lemon, lime, any type of vinegar, but those two items are missing in this recipe.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 129.991518,
                    "list": "['always good practice to taste your finished dish and adjust seasonings as necessary']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_60_4"
                },
                {
