                    "list": "['you want the pan to be warm enough to cook the egg but not too warm in that it browns the egg']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 331.861235,
                    "list": "['He should have allowed the skillet to get hot.', \"You notice when he poured the egg mixture in there, you didn't hear that sizzle.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 346.914231,
                    "list": "['He might have benefited from sauteing his garlic and his tomatoes first', \"He's going to have to take the egg out and let it sit\", \"Then probably reheat the egg once he's done sauteing the garlic and tomatoes\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 356.218228,
                    "list": "['continue cooking the uncooked egg by allowing it to seep into the extra space']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 366.349334,
                    "list": "[\"The important thing with cooking scrambled eggs is that they're not overcooked and they are not dried out.\", 'So you wanna look for that moist and shiny appearance on the outside of the eggs.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 397.763947,
                    "list": "['Some tomatoes are going to be juicier than others, especially if you have very ripe, larger tomatoes that you cut in quarters or wedges, as opposed to the cherry or grape tomato, which is not going to have as much liquid.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 402.942386,
                    "list": "['He wants his tomatoes to be very soft.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 425.057789,
                    "list": "[\"While he's sauteing this, his egg is over here getting cold.\", 'Now that egg is done.', \"So when he puts it back into the mixture, it's gonna be overcooked.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 428.727853,
                    "list": "['in off season where tomatoes may not be great', \"with these smaller tomatoes, they're not gonna put off as much that rich tomato flavor\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 437.048685,
                    "list": "['He should be putting this in another container and then putting it into the refrigerator, most likely a glass container with a fitting lid.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 500.153936,
                    "list": "[\"It's important to note that salt will also help counteract any bitterness from the tomato.\", 'If the tomatoes are bitter, one could use either salt or sugar to counteract that bitterness.', 'In addition, the salt is added to enhance the flavor of the dish.']",
