            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 15.189392,
                    "list": "['an easier way to do this would be to start with either a whole or half an onion', 'cut it in half, pull to pull, stem to root', 'make vertical cuts with the point of the knife towards the root', 'turn the onion 90 degrees and cut 90 degrees to the vertical cut']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 33.219185,
                    "list": "['By drawing this knife blade across the cutting board, you are dulling that knife blade each time that you draw it across the board.', 'A better way to do this would be to flip the knife over, use the spine of the knife to draw along the board, and to move anything around.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 79.027703,
                    "list": "['It is recommended that after each ingredient is cut or prepared that it be transferred to a mixing bowl.', 'This way you have the entire space of the cutting board to cut with and it will make it a lot easier to finish the tasks.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 101.486558,
                    "list": "['The preparer is having to use a slight sawing motion to cut through the tomatoes.', 'This is an indication that the knife blade is not sharp.', 'So it is recommended that any time cutting is being done that the user of the knife ensure that it is sharp at the beginning', 'if not, to use a sharpening stone or a sharpening tool to sharpen the knife.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 128.142886,
                    "list": "['It is a recommended practice to have a small bowl or other container readily available near your preparation area to put any scraps that are generated during the cooking process.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 136.193118,
                    "list": "['A safer way to do this would have been to cut lengthwise, place the flat halves of the cucumber on the cutting board, make your second lengthwise cut, and then cut across into the cubes.', \"The hazard, or the potential hazard, when trying to cut anything that is rounded is that the item you're cutting has the tendency to slip, and when that happens the knife can slip and cause cuts.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 151.11958,
                    "list": "['Mincing the cucumber will create mush', 'Destroying the integrity of the vegetable', 'For a salad, you want crunch or bite to the ingredients']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 258.822383,
                    "list": "['the salad appears to be missing half of the dressing components', \"you're going to want some sort of oil with the dressing, such as olive oil\", 'balance the oil with some sort of acid, such as red wine vinegar or fresh lemon juice', 'make any adjustments to the seasoning once everything is combined']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_010_3"
                }
            ]
        },
