                },
                {
                    "video_time": 17.281834,
                    "list": "['he puts a little too much power onto it and actually ends up reaching for it', 'the increase of his action has to increase to complete this rep']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 17.32358,
                    "list": "['The player should have more of a knee bend to bring the hips and body lower, allowing for greater flexibility and control in the first touch and movement after the ball.', \"The contact point on the ball with the receiving foot is not quite centered with the curvature of the foot. It's closer to the heel, which leads to a more inconsistent touch and less control.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 17.956906,
                    "list": "[\"Here focusing on the passing technique with the right foot, you'll see that the player is reaching for the ball, a straight leg, so although the toe is pointing down to the ground you'll see that the foot and the contact point with the ball is very narrow rather than being able to strike cleanly through the middle of the ball in the intended direction of it.\", \"Generally this becomes apparent because the non-kicking foot is not moving first with the line of the ball, so it's important that we get the non-kicking foot moving first, get our footwork right, so then we can get the kicking foot or the foot that's passing the ball with his knee closer to the position of the ball and then be able to make a cleaner contact and strike through to enable better control, accuracy, and power.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 17.974358,
                    "list": "['if he just took this touch inside with his right foot', \"he hit it too far so he's not controlling the the strength of his first touch back into the square\", \"This one's actually traveling outside of the square so that's a poor rep\", 'forces him to overextend with his kicking leg', \"he doesn't have any back lift in the leg to swing back and then swing forward\", 'contacting it with the toe box like the top of the toe as opposed to a little bit slightly more center of the foot toe box area']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 18.190224,
                    "list": "['Because the previous action the player was reaching for the ball with a straight leg', 'the foot that then lands on the ground after playing the pass now has to get reset, rebalanced before we can then move away into the space', \"What we'd want to see is if the non-kicking foot was closer for the initial pass and the knee was bent on striking the ball, that the player can strike through the ball and then return his foot back to a good position to then accelerate and move quickly into the space to receive the next pass\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
