                },
                {
                    "video_time": 34.323106,
                    "list": "['The non-kicking foot is relatively planted to the ground and the feet are pretty close together which would allow for less flexibility and freedom and speed to be able to move into the space with the ball.', 'The non-kicking leg is relatively straight which again is going to lead to a little less flexibility and movement after the touch.', 'We want this toe of the non-kicking foot maybe to start to turn a little bit more to the right which will open up the hips.', \"You'll see the hips here on receiving the ball are somewhat still relatively square. We'd want to try and start to turn our hips as we're receiving the ball which will then make it easier for us to travel in the same direction as the first touch to go.\"]",
