                    "list": "['This pass was impacted a little bit by the straightness of the right leg to play the pass with the right foot.', \"There's no follow through in the line of the direction of the pass to improve the weight and control.\", \"Here the player crosses his feet and side steps to the next receiving position which is effectively a slower movement. We'd prefer to see the player turn, face the direction he wants to go, move in a more natural forward running position after releasing the pass and then slow down and turn as the player receives it so the player is then set to receive the next ball.\"]",
