                {
                    "video_time": 71.476014,
                    "list": "['The player needs to work on receiving the ball properly and positioning it in the right area to make the next pass.']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 72.156215,
                    "list": "[\"The previous inside trap with the left foot was not quite up to standard in terms of touch, weight or movement to follow it up. The pass was received with the inside of the left foot and the touch went slightly backwards nearly over the subject player's right foot. This is an example of maybe a lower proficiency scored touch.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 74.387888,
                    "list": "[\"a player is reaching for the ball with a straight leg and doesn't get the knee closer to the line of the ball or over the top of the ball\", 'the contact point with the ball and the foot is closer to the little toe instead of the upper dorsal surface of the foot', \"the leg being outstretched restricts the player's ability to strike through and follow through in the line of the pass\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 77.074811,
                    "list": "['quite a misplaced pass that was played probably a little too far to his left']",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 77.626229,
                    "list": "['move non-passing foot with first touch', 'limit time between receiving the ball and playing the pass']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 80.770599,
                    "list": "[\"Again, try to pick up on when some of them go a little too far or don't go quite far enough and how that affects his pass.\", \"Something he can do to improve on is lowering his center of gravity. He's a little upright, so it makes it hard for him to do this touches more quickly.\", 'So to make it a challenge, see if you can do this faster.', \"Also, the player playing the ball into him can pass the ball harder to again challenge your first touch and increase the tempo of what you're doing.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "t5y5xs",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 81.586218,
                    "list": "['However, it should all be done a lot faster']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 81.649413,
                    "list": "['we want our movement into the next receiving action to be faster', 'the receiver is already in a more set position to receive the ball', 'the pass is not played with the accuracy as to where the receiver wants it']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 82.582734,
                    "list": "[\"The player receiving the ball wasn't ready or anticipating the pass coming in.\", \"He wasn't necessarily set well because of the placement of his non-kicking foot and the receiving foot are very close together.\", 'Our non-kicking foot starting to move away from the pass to allow our hips to open up so that we open up that space to receive the ball in.', \"We didn't get our feet set quickly to receive, you'll see that the foot of the receiving foot here, the left foot, is not necessarily in the heel down toe up position and the ball's direction is going towards the heel.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 83.269921,
                    "list": "['The first touch is too far underneath him.', \"He can't get enough back lift in this foot.\", 'The ball should be slightly out in front of him.']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 83.605408,
                    "list": "[\"The player doesn't get the ball out from under their feet, it ends up being under them, requiring a second touch and slowing them down.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 90.084256,
                    "list": "['player over hits the ball', 'pass that is played is inaccurate and too slow']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 92.200538,
                    "list": "['Player does not push the ball out of their feet far enough, slows them down, makes them have extra steps.']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 101.456077,
                    "list": "['only one step versus a shuffle where we saw at the start of the video']",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 103.961486,
                    "list": "[\"his first touch doesn't take him in the space where he can then move quickly onto the ball to play the pass.\", \"what we want to see with the first touch is as he's opening his body up to move in the direction with the ball is that he takes a positive first touch forward into the space\", 'which allows him to really step into the next pass which will then allow him to have better success, control and quality with the pass moving back into the receiver.']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 104.275815,
                    "list": "['The player has to push the ball out of their feet more']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 108.462604,
                    "list": "['The stance can still be corrected to be a little bit lower so they can move their feet faster.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.143964,
                    "list": "['The player needs to move into position quicker to receive the ball', 'so they can get their knees, hips, shoulders all positioned correctly']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.248869,
                    "list": "['He should get on his toes and bend his knees to lower his center of gravity for a more ready stance to receive the ball.']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.354825,
                    "list": "['increase the speed of movement', 'improve preparation by being on the balls of the feet', 'improve mental readiness']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 110.771485,
                    "list": "['The player needs to start rotating their torso as they receive the ball so that they can already start the moving motion into the next action.']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 111.542758,
                    "list": "['Player should develop good habits of checking his surroundings and anticipating his next action after passing the ball.']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 113.598,
                    "list": "['without taking speed into account', 'right foot just had to take one step']",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 114.039,
                    "list": "['The player pushed the ball too far out of their feet this time.']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 116.115542,
                    "list": "['poor example of touch weight', 'ideal landing space for the first touch']",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 116.705434,
                    "list": "[\"person didn't get the ball out of their feet and slow down the next action of the pass.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer06_2"
                }
            ]
        },
