                {
                    "video_time": 109.721766,
                    "list": "['When making a classic omelet, generally two to three eggs are used rather than one individual egg.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 113.948583,
                    "list": "['Onion should be sauteed separately, removed from the pan, and then the omelet made', 'Sauteed onions could be put inside the omelet if it is folded over in half', 'Sauteed onions could be added into a slit in a classic French omelet']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 115.479059,
                    "list": "['However, he failed to throw away the shell of his eggs. Egg shells are actually very dirty and they contain a lot of bacteria. So when you crack an egg, you immediately want to throw it into the garbage rather than setting it on your workspace.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 126.27065,
                    "list": "['using an egg mixture that only contains one full egg']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 135.462926,
                    "list": "['He adds too much paprika for the egg mixture. It should be a smaller amount.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 142.920793,
                    "list": "['I would always recommend using a fork or a whisk in this scenario since you could incorporate more air into the egg mixture with a fork or a whisk and make your omelet fluffier.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 147.266966,
                    "list": "['A better way to do this would be to use a fork or a balloon whisk. That would give you better mixing of the egg so that the white and the yolk are mixed together adequately.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 172.120723,
                    "list": "['I would not recommend using a pan this large unless it was all that you had to use.', \"It is more helpful when you're able to gauge the size of the pan based on the volume of omelet that you're going to be putting inside of it.\", 'The edges of a pan, this one not having any edges, is prohibitive.', 'The edges are very helpful in forming the true shape of the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 178.242132,
                    "list": "[\"The pan should be heated on a low or low medium heat so that when the egg is added, you don't hear any sizzling.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 184.212337,
                    "list": "['Here he could benefit from spreading out that egg mixture into a more even layer.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 194.859888,
                    "list": "['grab the flat spatula earlier']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 195.636409,
                    "list": "[\"That is uncooked egg. Some of its colored by the spice, but it's uncooked egg\", 'So that is still needing to like really solidify']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 196.728491,
                    "list": "[\"He should allow his omelet to form more of a base before he attempts to flip it so it doesn't break.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 202.385248,
                    "list": "['What should be done here is using a rubber spatula or a wooden spoon, the egg mixture should be gently stirred until the curds of the egg start to form. Once that occurs, you just gently cook the egg until it is finished cooking. Then you can fold or roll the omelet, adding any appropriate fillings at that time.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 204.601155,
                    "list": "['He should try to let the egg set in one place before moving it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 208.900284,
                    "list": "[\"He's having a very hard time getting it to stay on the spatula.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 211.885574,
                    "list": "['Sometimes the particulates of vegetables need to be broken out a little bit.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 217.362243,
                    "list": "['His first attempt to flip this is unsuccessful.', \"He didn't have a good enough grip.\", \"It's still got too much raw on top so it can be very messy.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 217.547883,
                    "list": "[\"He hasn't let it cook long enough\", \"Hasn't spread out the mixture enough for it to be ready to flip\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 220.147671,
                    "list": "['He needs to allow it to form more of a stronger base.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 223.450733,
                    "list": "[\"He's having to chase his omelet around the pan\", \"you can see here it's actually touching the wall because the pan has no sides\", \"He doesn't have anything to use as leverage to get the omelet up\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 228.883836,
                    "list": "[\"He didn't allow it to form a stronger base\", \"He's going to reshape the egg with a spatula\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 230.523239,
                    "list": "['The raw egg dumps onto the pan and kind of creates a mess.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 231.01858,
                    "list": "['His center of the omelet was very raw']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 231.321399,
                    "list": "['a classic omelet should never be flipped over', 'the heat should be much lower so that you avoid any browning of the eggs']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 239.606524,
                    "list": "['Continue to remove the egg to avoid it from sticking.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 244.486577,
                    "list": "['Flipping the omelet multiple times can cause it to break apart. Make sure to flip it only once or twice.', 'Practice proper flipping technique to ensure a smooth and intact omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 245.731739,
                    "list": "[\"This step of flipping the omelet over and over and over again is really unnecessary. You need to let an omelet cook on both sides, you know, one or two minutes per side until the egg mixture is cooked and that's enough. The flipping is unnecessary.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 245.96734,
                    "list": "[\"He's continuing to flip it, which is unnecessary.\", \"He doesn't need to move it.\", 'It would only need to be on once on each side.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 248.253866,
                    "list": "['pressing the omelet is only going to remove any nice fluffing air', 'make it a more dense omelet', \"you don't want to do that\", 'over attending to his omelet']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 256.587536,
                    "list": "['The omelet should be gently cooked so that there is no browning at all using a much lower heat.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 281.337887,
                    "list": "['Flips it again. At this point the egg is over cooked. The omelet is over cooked.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 285.16117,
                    "list": "[\"It's not a standard French omelet that would be not cooked on both sides.\", 'It would be cooked only on one side and then either folded or rolled.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_32_1"
                }
            ]
