            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 36.994881,
                    "list": "['The pan that has been selected is too large for a one-egg omelet.', 'Omelets are made with two to three eggs, not just a single egg.', 'The pan should be approximately six to eight inches or 15 to 25 centimeters.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.932684,
                    "list": "['Begin by gathering all of the tools and ingredients before starting the cooking process.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.932684,
                    "list": "[\"He should wait to start the heat after he's either already gathered his tools and ingredients or finished mixing his omelet mixture.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 50.776177,
                    "list": "[\"Typically, you want to have the omelet size fitting to the pan's base diameter.\", 'a little bit more slope size would be helpful here.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 57.547302,
                    "list": "[\"he's adding the oil and cutting on the pan too soon.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 63.289438,
                    "list": "['starting with an omelet']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 63.590129,
                    "list": "[\"This could be ghee also, but I'm not quite sure.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 65.30517,
                    "list": "['While oil is completely acceptable for making an omelet, the classic way for making an omelet would be to use clarified butter as your fat.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 78.662026,
                    "list": "['have all of your ingredients either grabbed or mixed together before you start the heat of the pan.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 87.810897,
                    "list": "[\"It's very unique, not something I've ever seen before, but it can be a good idea.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 90.101343,
                    "list": "['using a dice on his onion']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 94.508296,
                    "list": "['He puts his hand directly under the blade of the knife. This is a major mistake.', 'He should have gathered the chopped peppers to the side and then transferred them to the bowl.', 'This indicates a lack of knowledge of how to appropriately use the tools in this recipe.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 94.645173,
                    "list": "[\"Here he's gone underneath his blade to retrieve his pepper, which is a terrible idea. No one wants to lay a knife on their hand or the blade down. So you want to avoid doing things like this. It's not very safe.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 105.539068,
                    "list": "['He should take the skin off the onion before chopping it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 108.415953,
                    "list": "[\"He needs to be more careful tucking his fingers when he's handling that blade on top of that cutting board. He can potentially cut off the tip of his finger.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 109.389245,
                    "list": "[\"Now he's continuing to cut with the papery skin on the outside, I wouldn't recommend continuing that.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 111.074643,
                    "list": "[\"Once the ends of the onion have been cut off, it's advisable to remove the outside skin of the onion prior to chopping it.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 113.807618,
                    "list": "['You want to remove the skin and throw it in the garbage or remove it from your cutting surface.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 117.316966,
                    "list": "['But he does not have the papery skin removed. So he is now pressing that into every onion slice as he cuts. You always want to remove that. It is inedible.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 129.729333,
                    "list": "['Here you see that the chopping of the onion is a bit haphazard.', 'So the size of the pieces of onion are not uniform.', 'What is recommended is any time vegetables are being added to a dish is that they are cut in a uniform size.', 'What this does is allows them to cook at the same time.', \"So they'll be finished cooking all around the same time.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 134.152469,
                    "list": "['he should have thrown away the skin']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 152.644991,
                    "list": "['He probably could have just put the egg in the bowl with the onions and pepper.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 153.014281,
                    "list": "['Most people saut\u00e9 their vegetables before adding them to the egg mixture to make them softer.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 153.72853,
                    "list": "['You could also crack it on the edge of the bowl or the countertop, but cracking it with the spoon above the bowl eliminates any egg getting on your countertop or workspace.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 154.008371,
                    "list": "['Be mindful of sanitation and avoid cross-contamination by not placing eggshells on surfaces where raw food is present.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 160.189929,
                    "list": "['I would recommend only up to a fourth of a teaspoon of salt.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 169.941879,
                    "list": "['Add more seasoning to the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 170.187216,
                    "list": "['If it were red pepper that was crushed it would be quite hot.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 179.341819,
                    "list": "[\"It would be appropriate at this step as he's mixing his egg mixture to form the omelet to now cut on the heat on the pan.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 183.75232,
                    "list": "['also with one another']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 186.824748,
                    "list": "['...in mixing this omelet or this egg mixture using a fork or a whisk would have been more appropriate tool than a spoon.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 188.257783,
                    "list": "['The vegetable should be sauteed separately and then added to the omelet at the end', 'Use a fork or a whisk, like a balloon whisk, for better mixing']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 201.600725,
                    "list": "['tipping the pan to let the oil spread more evenly over the full surface']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 213.580013,
                    "list": "['Pour the egg mixture in a way that it evenly covers the entire pan.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 219.903273,
                    "list": "['The pan is too hot when you hear the sizzling sound. Warm your fat over low heat for better results.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 226.377541,
                    "list": "[\"His mixture is uneven and he didn't spread it out\", 'His pan was very hot prior to him adding the egg mixture', \"I always recommend cutting on the pan after you've assembled or mixed all of your ingredients\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 230.689436,
                    "list": "['He needs to let it form a base.', \"If he messes with it too much longer before it's formed a base, the egg will break.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 232.229668,
                    "list": "[\"Using a spatula to test the edges of the omelet and make sure they're not sticking.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 255.684503,
                    "list": "['If his pan had steeper sides, he would actually have a little leverage to go against the sides.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 259.063552,
                    "list": "['He seems to be really struggling with getting the entire omelet underneath to be on the flat spatula so that he can flip it.', 'I believe that this is because there is a concentration of heavy and wet ingredients in the center of the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 263.611201,
                    "list": "['Some of the uncooked egg from the center is popped off the center of the mixture.', \"Now it's beginning to cook as it's kind of pouring off of the omelet.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 265.838182,
                    "list": "['He could have let it sit for a little longer just to strengthen up that base']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 267.040681,
                    "list": "['when making a classic omelet, add your eggs to a six to eight inch or 15 to 20 centimeter saute pan or omelet pan', 'once the egg is finished cooking, you can either add your filling and then fold the omelet in half or roll your omelet in thirds and then cut a slit in the top']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 267.426714,
                    "list": "['He might have needed to wait longer for the egg to cook through more because obviously it was not cooked enough not to make this mess.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 268.916973,
                    "list": "['considering how much he moved when he played the round with it while it was forming the base']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 275.618211,
                    "list": "[\"I don't recommend this pressing on an egg mixture like this\", 'You want it to be nice and fluffy, a lighter texture', \"This will create a more dense mixture because you're pressing out any of the air\", 'It also is typical of a novice cook to press things like this', 'Having a little bit more patience and knowing that the mixture will cook through']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 279.415354,
                    "list": "[\"He flips it 10 or 20 more times in rapid succession. This indicates to me that he doesn't have a very strong knowledge of how to cook an omelet.\", 'You really only need to flip it one time, cooking on the underside and then flipping it to complete cooking of any raw ingredients on the other side.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 284.578859,
                    "list": "['He could just take it right on off the skillet instead of open-gucking it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 287.558663,
                    "list": "['He needs to just take it right on off the fire.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 288.169117,
                    "list": "['The individual continues to flip the omelet over a number of times', 'Pressing on the omelet using the spatula', 'Creating a very tough omelet', 'Overcooking the eggs', 'Scrambled eggs become very rubbery and dried out when overcooked']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 288.92281,
                    "list": "[\"This flipping and pressing over and over is a very unnecessary step and indicates to me that he isn't efficient with this particular task.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 292.3043,
                    "list": "[\"That's a lot of flips for an arm.\", \"Usually, you know, you got one flip on one side and one flip on the other. But he's having a flip fast at this moment.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 292.924236,
                    "list": "['He needs to move it to a plate instead of continuing to turn it and press it.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 298.326361,
                    "list": "['I mean the egg is completely done', 'I guess he must in a little darker']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 314.55315,
                    "list": "['One more flip.', 'Egg is completely done.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 318.466899,
                    "list": "['He must really mop that egg well done.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 319.36784,
                    "list": "['The goal is to have no browning of the egg at all.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_30_1"
                }
            ]
