            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 2.884444,
                    "list": "['An improvement the player can make looking on the right frame is bringing his ball placement position towards his shoulder area.', 'Preferably above his shoulders to create more security and ball control on the finish.', 'Also creating a closer gap to release the ball quicker towards our target area on the backboard.', 'And also creating separation from opposing defenders in a game-like scenario.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 3.059534,
                    "list": "[\"He's keeping that knee low so he doesn't reach his highest point of his jump.\", \"He's probably concerned about if he jumps to his highest capability, he runs the risk of jumping into this wall.\", 'He just decided not to give his maximum effort on the jump.', 'Ideally, when we do a reverse layup, we want to give maximum effort on the jump.', \"As we explode off this left leg, we really get that knee up high to our waist level to ensure that we're actually reaching the highest point of our jump.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bsgo5b",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 3.516471,
                    "list": "['After the release, allowing the ball to develop a proper angle', 'it needs to hit our target area and to have the opportunity of dropping inside the rim, resulting in a completed layup attempt']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 7.941896,
                    "list": "['Improvements the offensive player can make before going into his initial drive, as we look on the right frame, is getting his body placement position lower in the athletic stance to help create more balance on his drive, more explosiveness going into his jump towards the right side of the rim, and also allowing the player to have a quicker drive getting to the rim.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 8.459203,
                    "list": "[\"let's have a more explosive one dribble move\", 'I probably would be dribbling with my left hand', 'you want that dribble to be out in front of you', \"he's stepping right and then possibly stepping left here\", \"he's not looking at the ball when he dribbles, his eyes and head are up\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 8.684824,
                    "list": "['Improve body placement in an athletic stance to avoid getting pushed off position', 'Stay low during the gather to maintain balance on the attempt towards the rim']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 8.91199,
                    "list": "['I really feel like his movement, that dribble, those steps could definitely be more aggressive so that he could explode and lift his body up into his shot and be, you know, just be more aggressive overall.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 9.648734,
                    "list": "['The arm should be a little bit straighter and more direct.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 15.246089,
                    "list": "['To avoid turnovers, bring the ball placement position above the shoulders', 'Increase ball control and security going into the finish', 'Create a quicker gap to release the ball accurately towards the target area']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 15.351734,
                    "list": "['Steps to be more direct and aggressive', 'Lift his body up', 'Movements need to be explosive']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 22.315513,
                    "list": "['make sure that we have good side spin on the ball as we release it']",
                    "expert_uid": "bsgo5b",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 22.350761,
                    "list": "['Again, you can kind of see that shooting arm go out.', \"He's kind of hooking it, if you will.\", 'He shoots over his body instead of getting that shooting hand behind the ball and having more of a direct path here.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 28.019484,
                    "list": "[\"the wall here, I think it's causing his angle to be a little bit low versus typically it'd be up higher\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "ec8x25",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 28.502981,
                    "list": "[\"let's be more explosive\", 'really push off that left foot and lift the body up']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 28.636748,
                    "list": "['I would square this right shoulder up a little bit.', \"He's kind of hooking it, so he's got a really long distance to go here.\", 'Get that shooting hand a little bit more behind the ball', 'Shoot it more in front of you instead of out from you.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 29.024038,
                    "list": "['On this position here we have to be careful not to put too much side spin on the ball.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bsgo5b",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 34.830291,
                    "list": "['we want the player to bring his ball placement position above his shoulders', 'allowing more ball control and more security on the finish', 'a quicker release towards the target area']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.163968,
                    "list": "['square this right shoulder up more.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.375192,
                    "list": "[\"The player's body momentum is bringing him away from the basket, which does not allow him to properly give the ball the right amount of force, arc, and power it needs to get above the rim.\", 'Instead, the ball hits the side of the rim and bounces out, resulting in an incomplete layup attempt.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.475285,
                    "list": "['this attempt would need a little more side spin on it', 'since he did not get enough side spin on the ball, it ended up hitting the front of the rim', 'the further away from the square it is, the more side spin is needed for this spin and reach the basket']",
                    "expert_uid": "bsgo5b",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.758727,
                    "list": "['we will want the player to jump towards the rim', 'allowing a higher probability of guiding the ball properly towards our target area', 'with the right amount of power and arc it needs to get above the rim']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 40.434092,
                    "list": "['improve on body placement position', 'be lower to the ground', 'be quicker, more balanced, and more explosive on the jump', 'drive towards the right side of the rim']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.036928,
                    "list": "['maybe bend the knees and drop the hips a little bit', \"shooting elbow out. We'd like it to be in and under the ball\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 47.280568,
                    "list": "[\"making sure the defender's on your bottom side\", 'shielding the defense off on the top side']",
                    "expert_uid": "ec8x25",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 48.534793,
                    "list": "['attack this basket more aggressively', 'get the elbow in', 'have a follow through with an extended elbow', 'put your body between a defender and the ball']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 55.025331,
                    "list": "['But I think he could explode even more up if that dribble would take him to the basket more aggressively.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 61.685035,
                    "list": "['I love that he would square this right shoulder here and shoot more out in front of him.', 'Just to be more accurate, you want to bring it in a little tighter.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_18"
                },
                {
