                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 224.275236,
                    "list": "[\"making sure it's evenly coated with his dressing and his salt and pepper\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                }
            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 9.967466,
                    "list": "['This practice of drawing that blade across the cutting board will dull the blade.', 'When cutting, you want the sharpest knife possible to prevent any injury.', 'A dull knife is more likely to slip and cause a cut, whereas a sharp knife generally will not slip while cutting.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 15.464033,
                    "list": "['He should try to avoid throwing away ingredients.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 17.516834,
                    "list": "['It does not have to be a bag. It can be a bowl or any other type of small container.', 'This way you collect everything and then at the end of the cooking process you can go ahead and dump out.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 27.562847,
                    "list": "['When making a cucumber salad it is not necessary to always peel the cucumber.', \"With the Persian cucumber, the hothouse cucumber, it's really not necessary to peel.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 47.191698,
                    "list": "['be careful with knife slipping', 'try to make even cuts']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 50.645695,
                    "list": "[\"He should have his tomatoes there and have everything within arms reach so he doesn't have to keep going back and forth to the cooler.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 58.914322,
                    "list": "['You can do a straight cut across, creating half moons or half circles.', 'Or you could make an additional lengthwise cut on each half and just cut it into small cubes.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 69.357716,
                    "list": "['He should be careful with the peeling process.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 114.443975,
                    "list": "['It is important to make sure that vegetables, or really any vegetables, should be washed prior to cutting.', 'This would prevent cross-contamination from any contaminants that end up on your cutting board.', \"It's also important for ready-to-eat foods, such as salads, where they're not going to be cooked.\", 'And any potential for contaminants be removed prior to cutting.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 121.015245,
                    "list": "['The cut of that first tomato is indicative of a dull knife.', 'So a sharp knife will allow you to go through the skin of the tomato all the way through to the cutting board so that separation manually is not needed.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 137.122792,
                    "list": "['When you have round objects like this, you want to make sure that you have a sharp knife.', \"You don't want to have an incident where the knife rolls off of the tomato and then cuts you.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 196.632647,
                    "list": "['Freshly ground black pepper is the best way to enhance the flavor.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 201.087772,
                    "list": "['You can also add other dried herbs or fresh herbs or even some allium, such as shallots or red onion or scallions.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 202.642084,
                    "list": "['Hopefully add some acidity to that.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 211.101364,
                    "list": "[\"it's still important once the salad is mixed to ensure that it is tasted to make sure that all the seasonings are well balanced\", 'because there was additional salt and pepper added.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "sfu_cooking_008_3"
                }
            ]
        },
