                    "list": "[\"Looking at the player's initial start on the right frame, going into his right-handed miking layup attempt, an improvement that can help the player become more powerful, balanced, and explosive going towards the rim is having his body placement position lower in an athletic stance.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_17"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 1.947416,
                    "list": "['Another improvement that can help the player prevent potential turnovers in the game-light scenario is bringing his ball placement position towards his shoulder area, preferably above his shoulders, allowing more ball security and control going into the finish, as well creating separation from opposing defenders in the game-light scenario. Having easy access of stripping the ball from the opposite player.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_17"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 1.947416,
                    "list": "['Another improvement that can help the player prevent potential turnovers in the game-light scenario is bringing his ball placement position towards his shoulder area, preferably above his shoulders, allowing more ball security and control going into the finish, as well creating separation from opposing defenders in the game-light scenario. Having easy access of stripping the ball from the opposite player.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_17"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 2.287492,
                    "list": "[\"Ideally, when we're doing the Mike and drill, as we're going up with our right hand, we want to lift this knee up to our waist area so that will help us to jump to the highest of our capabilities, which would then allow us to release the ball at a higher, higher in the air and at the maximum capacity of our jump.\", 'So you see as the ball is down here, if he maximizes his jump, instead of releasing the ball here, he will release the ball even a little bit higher and the higher we release the ball, the greater chance that we have of getting the shot over the defense without the defense blocking or contesting the shot.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bsgo5b",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_17"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 2.316724,
                    "list": "['I really would love for this gentleman to go basically a lot harder.', 'He kind of just kind of pushes off, not with a lot of emphasis on getting up off the ground.', 'I really feel like he could really lift and get up a lot higher.', 'I would love for him to shoot a little bit more square and straight onto the basket.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_17"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 3.940599,
                    "list": "['What can help the player become more explosive on his jump', 'Create a higher chance of the ball going towards our target point', 'Get the player lower in his body placement position in the athletic stance', 'Allow a quicker release towards the rim']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_17"
                },
                {
