                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 12.844129,
                    "list": "['The climber is unable to complete the first move', \"Climbing is always a relationship between speed and efficiency. If you're super efficient but pretty slow, you're probably going to run out of energy. But if you're super fast but inefficient, you're probably going to make a mistake, which will lead to a loss of energy as well.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_4"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 13.212519,
                    "list": "['instead of getting his feet up and walking them up he just kind of locks his arms off', 'causing him to kind of drop away from the wall', \"now he's got to rework to gain his feet\", \"all of that he's clearly taking all of his weight to his arms\", \"so he's pulling more with his arms and losing tension with his feet\", 'all that repeated load on his arms is going to cause him to over grip and over pull']",
                    "expert_uid": "kz25yw",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_4"
                },
