                    "list": "[\"she's got a metal spatula with a nice wide top on it\", \"she's got it underneath her omelet\", 'She waited a while to let it cook further on that base.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 238.182631,
                    "list": "['Notice when she flipped the omelet, how the base part of it stays intact.', 'The bottom still stays intact.', 'The base of your omelet is still intact.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 240.607192,
                    "list": "['The base of the omelet stays intact when she flips it over', 'She got a nice base under her omelet']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 244.26762,
                    "list": "[\"She's loosening the omelet from the pan.\", \"It doesn't seem to be sticking\", 'she is pushing her spatula well underneath it']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 250.640928,
                    "list": "['She has a nice crust on the bottom of her arm, a nice base.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 260.639922,
                    "list": "['she has turned the omelet one time', 'let it cook on the other side for two to three minutes', 'should be done at that point']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 288.429138,
                    "list": "['Even on the second flip, the top part of the omelet stayed in place.', 'So she got a nice base on her omelet.', 'All her ingredients are in it.', 'It stayed intact.', 'She did a pretty good job making that omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 294.966667,
                    "list": "['cuts off the heat', 'ready to serve the omelet']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                }
            ],
            "tips_for_improvement": [
                {
                    "video_time": 9.821618,
                    "list": "['The pan appears to be too large to properly make an omelet in.', 'Instead, something on the order of six to eight inches in diameter with maybe a one inch side on it, also referred to as an omelet pan, should be chosen.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 18.411987,
                    "list": "[\"A better choice here would be a chef's knife.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 34.330678,
                    "list": "[\"You can see that she's cutting her onion half into slices, but as you can also see, her fingers are exposed to the blade of the knife. I would recommend tucking your fingers up underneath your knuckles so that the knuckles are up against the side of the knife, not the fingers.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 36.182737,
                    "list": "['making the cuts more precise and uniform']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 40.314831,
                    "list": "['Be careful while cutting the onion to avoid cutting off too much']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.611587,
                    "list": "[\"She might need to have better placement of her fingers so she doesn't slip and nick herself\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.374071,
                    "list": "[\"I would recommend either stepping off the block or having an elevated workspace so that she could more easily cut and not have to lean over as she's doing here.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 53.523813,
                    "list": "[\"She would be more efficient to go ahead and just make her cuts in the exact same style she's doing it into the whole half of the onion, flat side down, making long cuts, turning the entire group, and then cutting those crosswise. Then that will be a full dice, so she doesn't have to do so many little pieces at a time.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 102.540604,
                    "list": "['This step is a little out of order. First, you would want to add your egg to the mixture, so then you could determine how much seasoning you actually need to put in based on the liquid measure of the egg.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 116.668487,
                    "list": "['She should add the egg mixture first, then season it, and finally light the pan.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 118.749974,
                    "list": "[\"You don't want the pan to get too hot before you're finished mixing your eggs. If the pan is too hot, you risk pouring the eggs into the pan and having it burn before you can cut the heat down.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 121.581713,
                    "list": "['She should be careful not to place the pan directly over the heat to avoid burning the food.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 136.344108,
                    "list": "['I would recommend an eighth to a fourth of a teaspoon max.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 136.344108,
                    "list": "['using too much salt']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 140.54117,
                    "list": "['Instead of cracking the egg directly into the raw vegetables, saute the vegetables in oil or clarified butter.', 'Remove the sauteed vegetables from the pan and set them aside before preparing the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 140.651729,
                    "list": "['whisking the eggs before getting it in the hot skillet']",
                    "expert_uid": "nsikvp",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 147.749337,
                    "list": "['To make an omelet, you want to separate the eggs from the vegetables.', 'The omelet is going to require you to fold those vegetables in to create that layer for the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "nsikvp",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 153.245153,
                    "list": "['I would recommend using either a fork or a whisk instead to incorporate air into the omelet mixture and give it more volume.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 155.743674,
                    "list": "['She might want to whisk this a little bit or just go more vigorously in a stirring motion.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 168.587592,
                    "list": "['Use clarified butter instead of hair oil for a traditional omelet.', 'Clarified butter will prevent browning of the underside of the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 170.260896,
                    "list": "['If you added oil or ghee to her pan, ghee is clarified butter with the fats removed, this is going to be a barrier between her omelet and the pan.', \"It also helps to really solidify any nonstick surface so that your egg doesn't stick because egg notoriously is very sticky.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 173.776246,
                    "list": "[]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 179.45382,
                    "list": "['Here it appears that she has not used enough oil to fully cover the entire pan, only the center section. I would recommend putting enough oil in so that the entire bottom of the pan is coated.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 189.354603,
                    "list": "['Make sure to pour the mixture evenly to cover the entire diameter of the pan.', 'To create a perfect circle, make sure the mixture reaches the edges of the pan.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 192.670083,
                    "list": "['The pan is too hot when the egg is added, the heat needs to be lowered down.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 199.12449,
                    "list": "['just a little more, just a little oil, just a little bit further from the circumference of the egg.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 202.663138,
                    "list": "['A classic French omelet would never be done in a pan that gave it a free form edge because the beauty of it is a lot in the perfect circle.']",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 209.184981,
                    "list": "['The omelet may need to cook for longer on each side.', 'The participant should use a measuring cup to ensure the right amount of liquid for the omelet.']",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 221.266034,
                    "list": "['The individual is allowing the egg mixer to spread out into a very thin layer.', 'In making a classic omelet, one would gently stir the curds or the egg until it forms soft curds.', 'At that point, the stirring stops and you continue to cook the egg on very low heat until it is set.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 237.133321,
                    "list": "[\"Normally here when you make an omelet, you don't want to flip, you want to fold.\", 'Rather than cooking the egg all the way through, you kind of want to slow cook that egg to leave it slightly runny on top.']",
                    "expert_uid": "nsikvp",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 240.607192,
                    "list": "[\"The top part is not fully done, it's still moist\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "7kevm3",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 249.813165,
                    "list": "[\"It's moved away from being circular. Not ideal. You definitely would like it to be more of a circular shape.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 253.0236,
                    "list": "['Here, the omelet has been flipped over and once flipped, you can hear sizzling again in the pan. So with a classic omelet, you do not flip the omelet. You just allow it to cook as it is inside the pan.', 'Secondly, the temperature is still too hot on this pan, which is causing obvious browning on the outside of the egg, on the side that was just flipped over.']",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 285.705013,
                    "list": "[\"I'm not certain why she flipped it for the second time. Maybe she noticed that there was some egg mixture that went uncooked on the first side, but this step of flipping it a second time is unnecessary.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "rj74x8",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 290.045461,
                    "list": "['Here the omelet is being served flat onto the plate.', 'So an omelet should either be served folded in half and inside would be any sauteed fillings or cheese that the person preparing would desire.', \"If it is folded in thirds, which is the proper way for a French omelet, then once it's placed on the plate, a slit is made in the top of the omelet and that is where the sauteed vegetables or filling is placed.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "d2vast",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 292.968738,
                    "list": "[\"It's not a great looking masala omelet\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "bk8szu",
                    "video_name": "iiith_cooking_64_2"
                }
            ]
        },
