                {
                    "video_time": 23.445007,
                    "list": "['The climber hits this left hand a little inaccurately.', 'They bump a few times to get into their optimal position on the hold.', \"They're just inaccurate on this movement and have to tap it a few times to be able to control it again.\", 'The more times you have to pump on a hold, the harder the movement becomes. Try to establish the best spot with fewer taps.']",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_35"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 25.529642,
                    "list": "['The climber should try to hit each hold perfectly to conserve energy.', \"Making micro adjustments and milking the hold can tax the grip and wrist, so it's best to minimize these adjustments.\"]",
