                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_35"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 47.027471,
                    "list": "[\"Anytime you're going into a hold that only allows for one to two fingers, the goal is to enter that hold as controlled as possible and then weight it in a very controlled fashion to avoid injury or a shock load or suddenly put a lot of force on a single extended finger.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "50lpbg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_35"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 47.159056,
                    "list": "[\"A roll out move is when a climber is in a bunched position and maybe they're even grappling with their feet\", \"It's going from a tight position into a more open body, usually more comfortable body position\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "2vefmg",
                    "video_name": "uniandes_bouldering_012_35"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 55.311242,
