                {
                    "video_time": 34.615808,
                    "list": "[\"The inside touch to the left doesn't bring the ball across the body\", 'Feet are close together, making it harder to continue the ball on its trajectory', 'Back is slightly straight, limiting the ability to change direction quickly', 'Ball should travel further across to the outside line of the right foot']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 34.796006,
                    "list": "['It is a ball mastery pattern exercise that can be used to train players and to improve players.', 'It is pretty simple.', 'A good exercise to be taken away from this one.']",
                    "expert_uid": "7a277n",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 35.175419,
                    "list": "[\"the feet are still very close together, so as he's changing direction, his balance is going to be a little bit restricted\", 'his body is leaning in the direction that he wants to go next, which is going to help him transition into the next action', 'the contact on the ball being very close to his feet just limits him being able to accelerate and change speed in a game situation']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 39.498486,
                    "list": "[\"It's important to move the right foot away from the line of the ball when making contact\", 'The left foot should move faster and further away when rolling over the ball with the right foot', 'This will create a better balance and foundation for the player to accelerate away']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.317558,
                    "list": "['be a little bit lower in our hip placement and get our body lower to the ground, provide us a lower centre of gravity']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 42.376472,
                    "list": "['body being a little bit lower to the ground when moving faster']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 44.662801,
                    "list": "[\"The one thing we like to see if he's going to change direction is as he's dribbling the ball down this line is to position himself where he can step out a little further with the non-kicking foot, getting a lower set position so when he does change direction he provides himself the opportunity to accelerate into the space with speed.\", \"Because of the feet are relatively close together as he's changing direction, and you see the line of the ball with the feet, so he doesn't have any foundation to accelerate away, his body is in an upright position so it's just going to limit his ability to change speed and protect the ball if we're looking at a game situation.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 45.547949,
                    "list": "[\"The player's left foot is potentially too close to the ball and is making their knees close together, which can leave them out of balance.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 45.68128,
                    "list": "['This action with their left foot will allow them to turn their hips to the right and their shoulders to the right, allowing them to execute the action more quickly.']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 46.147942,
                    "list": "[\"As the players executed the turn, halfway through they've taken their foot off the ball and allowed the ball's momentum to roll out of their feet.\", 'This allows their right leg to then orientate itself, ready for its next action.']",
                    "expert_uid": "gnjtek",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 49.309287,
                    "list": "[\"He's not loaded in this far outside support foot as much as I would like to see him and lower his hips a little bit more.\", \"If he just got more bent down, lower descents, lower his stance, lower his center of gravity, he'll be able to push off in this direction much faster and be able to move at a much higher speed.\", \"Right now, because he's only moving at a slow, like a just slightly below average speed probably for him, that he's being much too upright with his stance.\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 51.03745,
                    "list": "[\"hips maybe could be a little bit slightly lower as we're approaching a change of direction\", \"as he's approaching the end of that dribbling sequence from cone A to cone B then we'll be looking for the player to slow down, get set, get into a lower position so he can protect and accelerate as he changes direction of the ball\"]",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 53.1728,
                    "list": "['he should bend his knee with his non-kicking foot to be more powerful and explosive', 'he should accelerate and separate from a defender with his next touch with the ball']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 53.733679,
                    "list": "['If he wants to increase his speed he really needs to be driving off of this leg much more.', 'His body would be a little bit lower to the ground actually as he pushed in this direction basically generating more force and more power into the ground.']",
                    "expert_uid": "3u75lz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 54.257126,
                    "list": "['this is a skill that we recommend when you have space and are defenders around', 'to push the ball with the laces and get into a running pattern with the ball just to be able to accelerate and attack space quickly']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 55.837441,
                    "list": "['if we can limit our touches to turn', 'takes fewer touches to go from one direction to the next', 'as soon as he takes that touch to turn, we want to see a player attack space with his next touch']",
                    "expert_uid": "umjlsz",
                    "video_name": "cmu_soccer16_2"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 59.958902,
                    "list": "[\"However, if we look on the left-hand side of the screen, the player's head is almost up straight.\", \"The player's head is nearly looking up level as he's dribbling.\"]",
