                    "expert_uid": "bsgo5b",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 4.844303,
                    "list": "[\"player's body's momentum is bringing him away from the basket\", 'did not give the ball enough power and arc to get above the rim', 'hit the top right corner of the backboard instead of the target area']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 10.742811,
                    "list": "['To prevent easy turnovers in game scenarios, the player should bring his ball placement position above his shoulder.', 'This will allow for more ball security and control going into the finish.', 'It will also allow for a closer gap to release the ball quicker towards the target area.', 'Lastly, this will provide separation from opposing defenders to prevent stripping or stealing the ball.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 10.845185,
                    "list": "[\"We'd love to see the shooter really, really push off a lot harder with that left foot.\", 'Maybe even take a bigger, bigger, stronger step on that left foot to get elevation and height to push this right knee up.']",
                    "expert_uid": "2g7km5",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 11.507797,
                    "list": "[\"The player's body's momentum is bringing him away from the basket, which does not allow the ball to gain enough arc and power to get above the rim hitting our target area.\", 'The ball is a little bit above our target area, giving it a different angle of dropping in the rim.', 'It does not provide the right amount of force and rotation it needs to develop the proper angle and will bounce off the rim, resulting in an incomplete layup attempt.']",
                    "expert_uid": "6jm95g",
                    "video_name": "unc_basketball_03-30-23_02_6"
                },
                {
                    "video_time": 11.515755,
                    "list": "['We do not want any side spin on the ball', 'If we put side spin on the ball while the ball made contact in this position on the backboard, it is going to spin off the backboard and we are going to miss the shot', 'If we are going to use side spin on the ball, we have to make sure that the ball makes contact on the line of the square or somewhere outside the square']",
